title: WATCH: Boykin strengthens Heisman case with clutch 69-yard TD run
text:
Updated Oct 11, 2015 at 12:05a ET 
Not so fast, Leonard Fournette. While the LSU running back is at the top of virtually everyone's Heisman list, Trevone Boykin is putting together a heck of a season for TCU . 
The Horned Frogs survived a scare from Kansas State Saturday night, and Boykin was the primary reason why. He threw for 301 yards, ran for 124 more and accounted for four touchdowns. 
With TCU trailing by five and time winding down in the fourth quarter, Boykin scampered for a gorgeous 69-yard touchdown to five the Frogs back the lead. 
After a Kansas State field goal tied the game at 45, Boykin would go on to throw the game-winning touchdown pass to Josh Doctson .
